timeline.bodyText:
Design consideration: I wonder if we should allow sending an Audit object without the createdBy pre-populated (to avoid having to use the UserSupplier in each class that needs to send audit).
The AuditManager can check if the createdAt is null and use the supplier to populate.
The design advantage is that we remove one dependency (UserSupplier) from  classes that need to use to create an Audit object. .
The send method of AuditManager would contain this snippet:
if ( StringUtils.isEmpty( audit.getCreatedBy() ) )
{
    audit.setCreatedBy( usernameSupplier.get() );
}

@mortenoh what do you think? (this is really a minor thing)

